    {
      "id": "b0506f61_7964ca89",
      "file_path": "catalog-model/src/main/java/org/openecomp/sdc/be/model/tosca/validators/TimestampValidator.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 52,
      "message": "https://yaml.org/type/timestamp.html , in order to admit \"no time zone (Z): 2001-12-15 2:59:43.10\" as a valid timestamp, I added this optional pattern",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7955,
        "name": "Francisco Javier Paradela Vila",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "javier.paradela.vila@est.tech",
        "username": "franciscovila"
      },
      "updated": "2022-07-15 08:03:43.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "c3d90b72_00478b06",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "68b587a3_9603818f",
      "file_path": "catalog-model/src/main/java/org/openecomp/sdc/be/model/tosca/validators/TimestampValidator.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 55,
      "message": "https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/time/format/DateTimeFormatterBuilder.html#appendOffset-java.lang.String-java.lang.String-\n\nIn order to admit \"space separated:  2001-12-14 21:59:43.10 -5\" as a valid timestamp, I added the optional Offset with whitespace literal plus pattern \"+H\" (the -5), \"+HH\" pattern wouldn be accepted here. The noOffsetText doesnt apply here, just must be not null. Moved to \"0000\" though",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7955,
        "name": "Francisco Javier Paradela Vila",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "javier.paradela.vila@est.tech",
        "username": "franciscovila"
      },
      "updated": "2022-07-15 08:03:43.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "e0d4dcdc_11f80c88",
      "unresolved": false
    },
